# Provisioning Cloud Storage with GCP

This project demonstrates how to provision and manage storage buckets in Google Cloud Platform using both the Cloud Console and `gcloud` CLI. Focus areas include IAM policy enforcement, object versioning, and lifecycle management.

## Features
- Created and configured Cloud Storage buckets with region-specific settings
- Applied fine-grained IAM policies to enforce least privilege
- Enabled versioning for object change tracking
- Implemented lifecycle rules to automatically delete or archive objects

## Tools & Technologies
- Google Cloud Platform (GCP)
- Cloud Storage
- IAM
- gcloud CLI

## Skills Demonstrated
✅ IAM & permissions  
✅ Cloud-native storage configuration  
✅ Policy-based resource management
